<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-22T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-22T15:00:00-05:00" n="522" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d522">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">821.51/3–2247: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-22T15:00:00-05:00">March 22,
                                    1947—3 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>161. Confidential for Braden. Rogers<note n="17" xml:id="d522fn1">James
                                Grafton Rogers, President of the Foreign Bondholders Protective
                                Council.</note> here on unpublicized exploratory mission on behalf
                            of Council to study possibilities of debt settlement. President
                                Ospina<note n="18" xml:id="d522fn2">Mariano Ospina Pérez.</note>
                            professes great interest in seeing matter cleared up but considerable
                            difficulty may be foreseen. While Rogers’ mission here is his
                            responsibility I propose to facilitate his task in every discreet way,
                            particularly in establishing his contacts and giving strong moral
                            support.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wiley</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>